From 46fe61b270534995e2149749f9ecb627238cc0b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Code <xpointsh@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 06:48:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: Add Oracle class witness markers A8-A12 for anti-LLM
 cheat detection
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the structural foundation needed by lsp-max-anti-cheat to identify and
classify LLM coding agent cheating patterns via OCEL-based process mining.

New module: src/witnesses_anti_cheat.rs
- OracleA8AuditLogTampering: receipts without ancestor computation events
- OracleA9TemporalAnomaly: events with impossible timestamps
- OracleA10CausalViolation: mutations/diagnostics without causal predecessors
- OracleA11UnknownCollapse: UNKNOWN state resolved without resolution event
- OracleA12CyclicDependency: cycles in the OCEL event causality DAG
- LspMaxSessionWitness: authority label for lsp-max session OCEL events
- AntiLlmScanWitness: authority label for anti-llm-cheat scanner OCEL events

Updated: src/diagnostic.rs
- Added five CompatDiagnostic variants (OracleA8–A12) with law descriptions
- Each variant names the violation law and its remedy
- Display impl extended with human-readable messages for all five Oracle classes

Updated: src/lib.rs
- Registered witnesses_anti_cheat module alongside existing witness families
- Marked as hand-authored (not ggen-generated)

These are structure-only additions — no engines, no algorithms. Oracle
inference runs in wasm4pm; this crate only names the authority classes.
The witnesses travel with Evidence values through the admission pipeline
so diagnostics can identify which Oracle class flagged a violation.

Used by: lsp-max/crates/lsp-max-anti-cheat (anti-cheat OCEL integration)
